ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The class was an exploration of different modes of montage and the uses and implications of those modes. Mediated between an exploration of an overarching theme--montage, and an analysis of specific directors' works and styles. I would recommend because the class really touched upon issues fundamental to film and the relationship between aesthetics and politics.
Sure. It is a great course for those who like early Soviet cinema, Marxism, post WWII experimental film, and F. Jameson.
